<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1483,2012]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,346,1599,1625]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Discussion:</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[493,667,1600,1625]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydrobaderia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[493,667,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hydrobaderia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced for a single specimen collected together with numerous representatives of 
<taxonomicName box="[486,800,1639,1664]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipalpis">
<emphasis box="[486,800,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hydryphantes crassipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a pond in 
<collectingCountry box="[984,1068,1638,1664]" name="Turkey" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ozkan" box="[1082,1230,1638,1664]" pageId="11" pageNumber="33" refString="Ozkan, M. (1985) Hydrobaderia n. gen., eine neue Hydryphantiden-Gattung aus der Turkei (Acari, Actinedida, Hydryphantidae). Entomologica Basiliensia, 10, 19 - 26." type="journal article" year="1985">
Özkan 
<number box="[1167,1230,1638,1664]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). As stated by the author and documented in his detailed description, it agrees with the latter species in all details, with the fundamental exception of the absence of a frontal shield as found typically in all species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1261,1429,1716,1741]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1261,1429,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hydryphantes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Instead, only a pair of elongated sclerotized rods is found in that area where typically two apodemes form the characteristic posterior extensions of the 
<taxonomicName box="[632,796,1793,1818]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[632,796,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hydryphantes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
frontal shield.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1483,2012]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Recently, the same phenomenon was detected in a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[980,1131,1832,1857]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">
<emphasis box="[980,1131,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. flexuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1208,1277,1832,1858]" name="Spain" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Spain</collectingCountry>
(see below). Obviously, occasionally the formation of a frontal shield may be suppressed by some kind of developmental disturbance and its absence is not a character suitable for the definition of taxonomic units. Therefore we consider 
<taxonomicName box="[258,404,1948,1973]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iliceansis">
<emphasis box="[258,404,1948,1973]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. iliceansis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[581,760,1948,1973]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipalpis">
<emphasis box="[581,760,1948,1973]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. crassipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, consequently, the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Ozkan, 1985" authorityName="Ozkan" authorityYear="1985" box="[1113,1436,1948,1974]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydrobaderia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1113,1278,1948,1973]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hydrobaderia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ozkan" box="[1285,1436,1948,1974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="33" refString="Ozkan, M. (1985) Hydrobaderia n. gen., eine neue Hydryphantiden-Gattung aus der Turkei (Acari, Actinedida, Hydryphantidae). Entomologica Basiliensia, 10, 19 - 26." type="journal article" year="1985" yearSuffix="a">
Özkan, 
<number box="[1377,1436,1948,1974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch, 1841" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1841" box="[317,629,1986,2012]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[317,481,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hydryphantes</emphasis>
Koch, 
<number box="[567,629,1986,2012]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1841.0">1841</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
